@startuml
!includeurl https://raw.githubusercontent.com/proveo-ca/identity/refs/heads/main/proveo.iuml
title Nightfall - Initial Version Component Diagram
' Pure Browser Experience - Godot 4 Web Export + Nano Models

package "Browser Runtime" {
  [Godot 4 Web Export\n(.html + .wasm + .pck)] as GodotWeb
  [WebLLM / Nano Models\n(q4f16_1 or smaller)] as NanoLLM
  [IndexedDB Cache] as Cache
}

package "Godot Engine (Core)" {
  [Main Scene\n(3-story house + basement)] as MainScene

  component "Player Character" as Player {
    [CharacterBody3D] as PlayerBody
    [Camera3D (First Person)] as FpsCamera
    [SpotLight3D (Flashlight)] as Flashlight
    [HeartRate System] as HeartRate
    [Inventory (Pockets)] as Inventory
  }

  component "AI Agents" as Cats {
    [Cat 1..4\n(CharacterBody3D)] as CatBodies
    [Nano Model Driver\n(Agentic Reasoning)] as CatBrain
    [Behavior Tree / State Machine] as CatAI
    [Vision (RayCast3D)] as CatVision
  }

  [Interactible Objects] as Interactibles
  [Items & Pickups] as Items
  [Environment\n(Lights, Curtains, Sounds)] as Environment
}

package "Nano Model Layer" as Nano {
  [Tiny LLM (e.g. Phi-2-q4, Gemma-2B, TinyLlama)\nrunning via WebLLM] as NanoLLM
  note right of NanoLLM
    Each cat gets its own
    very small context +
    personality prompt.
    Runs entirely in browser.
  end note
}

' Relationships
GodotWeb --> NanoLLM : "Loads & calls nano models"
GodotWeb ---------> MainScene : "Runs game"

MainScene -----> Player
MainScene -----> Cats
MainScene --> Interactibles
MainScene --> Items
MainScene --> Environment

PlayerBody --> FpsCamera
PlayerBody --> Flashlight
PlayerBody --> HeartRate
PlayerBody --> Inventory

Cats --> CatBodies
CatBodies --> CatAI
CatAI --> CatBrain
CatBrain --> NanoLLM : "Query for next action"
CatBodies --> CatVision

Interactibles --> Player : "Raycast interaction\n(notes, doors, buttons, curtains)"
Items --> Inventory : "Pick up → Pocket"

Environment --> HeartRate : "Affects BPM\n(sounds, darkness, cat proximity)"
Environment --> Flashlight : "Battery / Flicker"

note bottom of GodotWeb
  • Pure browser experience (no backend)
  • Godot 4.3+ Web export with WebGPU support
  • All AI runs locally via WebLLM nano models
  • 20-minute real-time survival loop
  • Final reveal: curtains open → cats are just troublemakers
end note

note right of CatBrain
  Initial approach:
  - Very small system prompt per cat
  - Simple goal-oriented behavior
  - Vision + sound events as context
  - State machine as safety net
end note

@enduml